This paper discusses the challenges in building conversational agents, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.CL and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of search and structured data, which falls under information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the experience of building a conversational agent, which falls under software engineering (SD) sub-category.
